01:37.836 --> 01:41.101
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.231 --> 01:43.451
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.581 --> 01:47.063
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:12.480 --> 02:14.395
-KAY: MITCH, THIS
IS SO NICE OF YOU,

02:14.525 --> 02:17.702
BUT I REALLY FEEL GUILTY ABOUT
TAKING THE AFTERNOON OFF.

02:18.355 --> 02:19.922
-GUILT FEELINGS? I LIKE THAT.

02:20.052 --> 02:21.315
-HEY!

02:21.880 --> 02:24.579
I'VE BEEN BUSTING MY BUTT
TRYING TO GET THIS PAPER GOING.

02:25.275 --> 02:26.494
YOU KNOW, I JUST WANT
THE VENICE VOICE

02:26.624 --> 02:27.582
TO STAND FOR SOMETHING.

02:27.712 --> 02:29.410
I WANT IT TO HAVE AN IMPACT.

02:29.540 --> 02:32.456
AND I WANT TO ADDRESS THE ISSUES
THAT AFFECT OUR COMMUNITY.

02:34.632 --> 02:36.199
A LAPTOP COMPUTER?

02:36.330 --> 02:37.940
-BORROWED IT FROM THE OFFICE.

02:38.723 --> 02:39.985
-WHAT FOR?

02:40.116 --> 02:41.422
-MITCH: YOUR LEAD STORY.

02:42.510 --> 02:43.989
-MY LEAD STORY?

02:44.120 --> 02:46.905
-THERE IT IS. THE
SAN DIMAS PIER.

02:48.080 --> 02:49.821
-WHAT ABOUT IT?

02:49.952 --> 02:51.649
IT'S CONDEMNED. I THOUGHT
THEY WERE GONNA TEAR IT DOWN.

02:51.780 --> 02:53.869
-THAT'S JUST IT, THEY'RE
NOT TEARING IT DOWN

02:54.652 --> 02:56.350
UNTIL THEY FIGURE OUT
WHO'S GONNA PAY FOR IT.

02:57.351 --> 02:59.875
THE OWNER'S HAVE FILED A
LAWSUIT, BUT BETWEEN THE COUNTY,

03:00.005 --> 03:01.616
THE STATE, THE OWNERS,
AND THE ATTORNEYS,

03:01.746 --> 03:03.661
THE WHOLE THING COULD BE
TIED UP IN COURT FOR YEARS.

03:03.792 --> 03:06.490
MEANTIME, IT'S A MAGNET
FOR EVERY MACHO SURFER

03:06.621 --> 03:07.709
TRYING TO SHOOT THE PIER.

03:08.623 --> 03:10.277
SEE THAT BLACK STUFF
AROUND THE PILINGS?

03:10.407 --> 03:11.843
-KAY: YEAH.

03:11.974 --> 03:14.890
-IT'S CALLED REBAR.
CUTS YOU UP REAL GOOD.

03:15.020 --> 03:17.414
-WHY DON'T YOU JUST CLOSE
DOWN THE BEACH IN THIS AREA?

03:17.545 --> 03:19.329
-IT'S A GOOD IDEA, BUT
WE DON'T HAVE THE MANPOWER

03:19.460 --> 03:21.375
TO PATROL THE AREA
24 HOURS A DAY.

03:22.419 --> 03:23.377
-I DON'T KNOW, MITCH.

03:23.507 --> 03:24.813
TO BE PERFECTLY HONEST WITH YOU,

03:24.943 --> 03:26.336
I DON'T THINK
THERE'S A STORY HERE.

03:26.467 --> 03:28.817
I MEAN, NOBODY CARES
ABOUT A COLLAPSING PIER.

03:31.559 --> 03:34.823
[WAVES CRASH]

03:35.606 --> 03:36.738
-HEY!

03:38.957 --> 03:40.089
-KAY: WHAT'S WRONG?

03:44.615 --> 03:46.226
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

03:53.755 --> 03:55.583
[WAVES CRASHING]

04:13.862 --> 04:15.603
IS HE ALL RIGHT?

04:16.908 --> 04:19.519
-YEAH. HE'S CUT. I DON'T
THINK IT'S TOO BAD, THOUGH.

04:19.649 --> 04:21.522
EASY, EASY, EASY. THERE YOU GO.

04:23.654 --> 04:24.438
DO ME A FAVOR.

04:24.568 --> 04:25.569
-ALL RIGHT.

04:25.700 --> 04:26.701
-PUT SOME PRESSURE RIGHT HERE.

04:26.831 --> 04:27.832
-UH HUH.
-MITCH: IT'S EASY.

04:27.963 --> 04:29.225
THAT'S IT. I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

04:29.878 --> 04:31.271
NEXT TIME READ THE
SIGNS, HUH, BUDDY?

04:33.447 --> 04:34.665
-IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

04:35.840 --> 04:37.059
IT'S GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.

04:39.191 --> 04:41.019
-ALL I KNOW IS THAT SOONER
OR LATER, SOMEBODY'S GONNA GET

04:41.150 --> 04:42.630
SERIOUSLY MANGLED
ON THE PILINGS.

04:42.760 --> 04:44.066
-MITCH, I UNDERSTAND
YOUR CONCERNS.

04:44.196 --> 04:45.633
I FEEL EXACTLY THE SAME WAY.

04:45.763 --> 04:46.895
I PUT IN A CALL TO THE
COUNTY COMMISSIONER.

04:47.025 --> 04:47.939
-WHAT DID HE SAY?

04:48.070 --> 04:49.506
-HE'S, UH, NOT IN.

04:50.638 --> 04:51.552
-BIG SURPRISE.

04:51.682 --> 04:53.118
-LOOK, MITCH,

04:53.249 --> 04:54.903
I KNOW THERE'S BEEN SOME
FOOT-DRAGGING ON THIS,

04:55.033 --> 04:56.383
BUT WE STILL HAVE TO WORK
THROUGH THE PROPER CHANNELS

04:56.513 --> 04:57.471
ON THESE MATTERS.

04:57.601 --> 04:58.994
-NOT ANYMORE.

04:59.124 --> 05:00.387
KAY MORGAN'S GONNA
RUN A FRONT PAGE STORY

05:00.517 --> 05:02.084
IN THE VENICE VOICE.

05:02.214 --> 05:03.607
-YOU THINK IT'S WISE TO
GET THE MEDIA INVOLVED NOW?

05:03.738 --> 05:05.392
-NOBODY'S LISTENING
TO US, CAPTAIN.

05:06.218 --> 05:07.655
MAYBE SHE'LL GET
THEIR ATTENTION.

05:07.785 --> 05:09.874
-WHAT IS IT WITH THESE
SURFERS TODAY, MITCH?

05:10.005 --> 05:11.876
I MEAN, WE NEVER HAD
TO PROVE ANYTHING.

05:12.007 --> 05:14.705
RUNNING A GAUNTLET OF SOME
BATTERED PILINGS? [CHUCKLES]

05:14.836 --> 05:16.838
I MEAN, IT WAS ENOUGH
JUST BEING OUT THERE,

05:16.968 --> 05:18.361
GETTING ON TOP OF A WAVE,

05:18.492 --> 05:20.145
FEELING THE POWER OF THE
WORLD UNDER YOUR BOARD.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.539
-HANGING TEN.
-HANGING TEN.

05:23.932 --> 05:25.586
-WALKING THE NOSE.
-WALKING THE NOSE.

05:26.413 --> 05:29.024
-[CHUCKLES] WOULD
YOU TWO FOLLOW ME?

05:29.154 --> 05:30.373
I'VE GOT SOMETHING TO SHOW YA.

05:38.599 --> 05:41.253
AH, THIS WAS MY FIRST
SURFBOARD, GENTLEMEN.

05:41.384 --> 05:44.387
A MICKEY DORA ORIGINAL,
COMPLETE WITH A HATCHET SKEG.

05:45.083 --> 05:47.521
THIS OLD PLANK AND I
GO BACK A LONG WAY.

05:47.651 --> 05:49.784
-LONGER THAN EITHER ONE OF
US CARE TO REMEMBER, EH, BEN.

05:49.914 --> 05:51.394
-[LAUGHS] YEAH.

05:51.525 --> 05:52.874
-YOU KNOW, I'LL NEVER
FORGET MY FIRST STICK.

05:53.744 --> 05:55.355
IT WAS A HAND-ME-DOWN
FROM MY BROTHER, BUZZ.

05:55.485 --> 05:57.313
BOY, COULD THAT BABY RIP.

05:58.401 --> 06:00.098
YOU KNOW, I OFFERED IT TO HOBIE,

06:00.229 --> 06:02.927
BUT HE SAID HE WOULDN'T BE
CAUGHT DEAD WITH AN ANTIQUE.

06:03.058 --> 06:04.755
SO I HAD TO GO OUT AND BUY
HIM ONE OF THOSE NEW JOBS,

06:04.886 --> 06:06.844
YOU KNOW, THE TRI-FINS
WITH THE GORILLA GRIPS.

06:07.410 --> 06:09.325
THAT DAMN THING COST
ME A WEEK'S SALARY.

06:09.456 --> 06:10.239
[LAUGHING]

06:10.370 --> 06:11.806
-TELL ME ABOUT IT, HUH?

06:11.936 --> 06:12.720
-AT LEAST THE WAVES
ARE STILL FREE, MITCH.

06:12.850 --> 06:13.808
-YEAH. WELL, SO FAR.

06:16.027 --> 06:17.638
[INSPIRATIONAL MUSIC]

06:26.386 --> 06:28.126
-SEE, FEEL THE MATERIAL.

06:28.257 --> 06:32.000
THE FINEST QUALITY IMPORTED
DIRECTLY FROM BRAZIL.

06:32.740 --> 06:37.092
THE BARGAIN OF A LIFETIME.
$25, TWO FOR $40.

06:38.398 --> 06:41.488
-EDUARDO! WHAT'S THE
SPECIAL OF THE DAY?

06:42.097 --> 06:43.838
-BIKINIS.
-EDDIE: AH.

06:43.968 --> 06:45.753
-MADE FROM A NEW
ORGANIC MATERIAL.

06:46.580 --> 06:48.103
ONE SIZE FITS ALL.

06:48.233 --> 06:49.844
PLEASE.

06:49.974 --> 06:51.802
YOU WILL LOOK EVEN MORE
BEAUTIFUL, IF THAT'S POSSIBLE.

06:51.933 --> 06:53.935
-I HAVE ENOUGH BIKINIS,
EDUARDO, THANK YOU.

06:54.936 --> 06:55.763
-SO, YOU GOT A PERMIT?

06:55.893 --> 06:57.504
-A PERMIT? OF COURSE.

06:57.634 --> 07:00.115
I'M A BUSINESSMAN. NATURALLY,
I WOULD HAVE A PERMIT.

07:00.245 --> 07:01.246
ONE SECOND, PLEASE.

07:05.250 --> 07:07.427
IT SEEMS I LEFT THIS
PERMIT IN MY CAR.

07:07.557 --> 07:09.124
-WELL, WHERE IS YOUR CAR?

07:09.254 --> 07:12.127
-UNFORTUNATELY, MY WIFE
DROVE IT TO THE DOCTOR'S.

07:12.257 --> 07:13.824
SHE'S VERY ILL.

07:13.955 --> 07:15.609
I HAVE TO SELL THESE
BIKINIS TO BUY HER MEDICINE.

07:15.739 --> 07:17.175
-ALL RIGHT. THAT'S
ENOUGH, EDUARDO.

07:17.306 --> 07:18.916
WE'RE GONNA LET IT
SLIDE THIS LAST TIME,

07:19.047 --> 07:20.309
BUT THAT'S IT.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.963
COMPRENDE?
-EDUARDO: ABSOLUTELY.

07:22.093 --> 07:24.531
I AM A LAW ABIDING CITIZEN.
I LOVE THIS COUNTRY.

07:24.661 --> 07:26.271
I WILL DO WHATEVER YOU SAY.

07:27.359 --> 07:30.711
LOOK, SEE, FEEL THE MATERIAL.

07:30.841 --> 07:34.497
THE FINEST QUALITY, IMPORTED
DIRECTLY FROM BRAZIL.

07:37.152 --> 07:38.022
-HEY.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.939
WHAT'S THE STORY HERE?

07:42.070 --> 07:43.114
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SUPPOSE TO CLEAN YOUR ROOM

07:43.245 --> 07:44.812
BEFORE WE LEFT.
-I DID.

07:44.942 --> 07:45.856
-YOU DID?

07:47.162 --> 07:48.032
WHERE?

07:50.252 --> 07:53.081
ALL RIGHT, JUST DO ME A FAVOR.

07:53.211 --> 07:55.649
MAKE YOUR BED AND I'LL HELP
YOU WILL ALL THIS JUNK.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.868
-WHY DO I HAVE TO MAKE MY BED

07:57.999 --> 07:59.653
WHEN I'M NOT EVEN
GONNA TO SLEEP IN IT?

07:59.783 --> 08:01.829
-YOU HAVE TO MAKE YOUR
BED BECAUSE I ASKED YOU TO.

08:01.959 --> 08:03.134
NOW COME ON, GET IT TOGETHER.

08:03.265 --> 08:04.309
I DON'T WANT TO
MISS THE CEREMONY.

08:05.223 --> 08:06.573
-THERE'S GONNA BE A CEREMONY?

08:06.703 --> 08:07.965
-THAT'S RIGHT.

08:08.096 --> 08:10.359
FIRST, WE MAKE A
SACRIFICE TO THE GODS,

08:10.490 --> 08:12.709
ASKING THEM TO BRING GOOD WAVES.

08:12.840 --> 08:14.276
-A HUMAN SACRIFICE?

08:14.406 --> 08:16.626
-WORSE. A CHERISHED SURFBOARD.

08:17.279 --> 08:20.935
ANCIENT RITUAL, HANDED DOWN
FROM ONE GENERATION TO NEXT,

08:21.065 --> 08:22.458
HA HA.

08:22.589 --> 08:24.025
SOMEDAY, YOU'LL PASS
IT ON TO YOUR SON.

08:24.155 --> 08:26.157
-UM, I DON'T THINK SO, DAD.

08:26.288 --> 08:28.638
I KINDA PLAN ON BEING
NORMAL, IF YOU DON'T MIND.

08:28.769 --> 08:31.511
-WHY, I OUGHTA [SCREAMS]

08:31.641 --> 08:32.773
[LAUGHING LOUDLY]

08:32.903 --> 08:34.644
TAKE IT BACK!
YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:34.775 --> 08:35.993
IF I SAID THAT TO MY FATHER,
YOU KNOW WHAT HE'D DO TO ME?

08:36.124 --> 08:40.171
HE'D DO THIS.
[EXCLAIMING LOUDLY]

08:40.302 --> 08:41.346
TAKE IT BACK!

08:41.477 --> 08:44.131
-I TAKE IT BACK.
I TAKE IT BACK.

08:44.261 --> 08:45.176
[PHONE RINGS]

08:45.307 --> 08:47.396
-OH. I GOT IT, I GOT IT.

08:47.527 --> 08:50.094
-HELLO? UH, YOU MUST HAVE
THE WRONG PHONE NUMBER.

08:50.225 --> 08:51.879
THERE'S NO ONE NAMED ROVER HERE.

08:52.009 --> 08:53.663
-WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT! THAT'S MY BROTHER.

08:53.794 --> 08:54.838
-UNCLE BUZZY?

08:54.969 --> 08:58.233
-BUZZ! YEAH. HOW
THE HELL ARE YA?

08:59.669 --> 09:00.627
WHERE THE HELL ARE YA?

09:02.324 --> 09:03.586
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'
IN SANTA BARBARA?

09:05.022 --> 09:07.198
[CHUCKLES] YEAH, WE'RE
HAVING THE CEREMONY.

09:08.025 --> 09:09.505
I'M WALKIN' OUT THE
DOOR IN TEN MINUTES.

09:10.201 --> 09:11.115
YEAH, TRACAS.

09:12.073 --> 09:13.291
-HOBIE: IS HE COMIN'?
-HE'S COMING.

09:13.422 --> 09:14.205
-YES!

09:14.336 --> 09:15.467
-SEE YA THERE! YEAH!

09:19.080 --> 09:20.342
-UH OH, NO!

09:22.431 --> 09:27.610
[WAVES CRASHING]
[FESTIVE DANCE MUSIC]

09:32.920 --> 09:34.661
-OH, MY GOD. HELLO, CAPTAIN.

09:34.791 --> 09:36.271
-MITCHELL, MITCHELL!

09:36.401 --> 09:38.229
-EH. KELLY, STAY IN
SHAPE, WILL YA? [LAUGHS]

09:38.360 --> 09:39.796
-HEY, MITCH.
-MITCH: HEY.

09:39.927 --> 09:41.232
-WHAT'S THIS ABOUT
YOUR BROTHER SHOWIN' UP?

09:41.363 --> 09:42.538
I THOUGHT HE WAS
LIVIN' IN NEW ZEALAND.

09:42.669 --> 09:44.192
-NEW GUINEA, NEW GUINEA.

09:44.322 --> 09:46.194
-OH. I KNEW IT
WAS NEW-SOMETHING.

09:49.197 --> 09:51.329
[MEN EXCLAIMING LOUDLY]

09:55.856 --> 09:58.206
-HEY, DAD. WHY DOES
UNCLE BUZZ STAY AWAY?

09:58.336 --> 10:00.425
I MEAN, HOW COME
WE NEVER SEE HIM?

10:01.339 --> 10:02.689
-REALLY DON'T KNOW, HOBE.

10:02.819 --> 10:04.212
HE LEFT HOME WHEN I
WAS ABOUT YOUR AGE.

10:04.342 --> 10:06.606
SAID HE WAS GONNA
FIND THE PERFECT WAVE.

10:07.432 --> 10:09.217
I THINK HE'S PROBABLY
STILL LOOKING FOR IT.

10:15.745 --> 10:16.703
[ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

10:18.748 --> 10:21.621
-HEY! I'M BACK!

10:22.752 --> 10:24.972
YOU! I WANT YOU! I AM BACK!

10:28.062 --> 10:30.064
[CROWD CHEERS]

10:33.458 --> 10:35.809
-UH, OH.

10:35.939 --> 10:37.332
[LAUGHING]

10:37.462 --> 10:38.768
-GIVE ME A LITTLE
SAMMY, A LITTLE SAMMY.

10:38.899 --> 10:41.989
-HEY, MAN. HOW ARE YOU?
IT'S GOOD THE BE BACK!

10:42.119 --> 10:44.208
GOD, IT'S GOOD TO SEE
YOU. WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

10:44.339 --> 10:45.427
ARE YOU STILL WITH, UH?

10:45.557 --> 10:46.994
-NO. NO WAY, ARE YOU SERIOUS?

10:47.124 --> 10:47.908
ARE YOU STILL--

10:48.038 --> 10:48.952
-NOPE. DONE DEAL.

10:49.736 --> 10:51.085
-NO, THIS CAN'T BE.

10:51.215 --> 10:52.695
HOBIE! COME HERE,
YOU LITTLE GREMMIE.

10:52.826 --> 10:53.740
[LAUGHS]

10:53.870 --> 10:55.002
HOW YOU DOIN', HOBIE, HUH?

10:55.132 --> 10:56.177
-HOW YOU DOIN', UNCLE BUZZY?

10:56.307 --> 10:57.439
-ALL RIGHT, BUDDY.

10:57.569 --> 10:58.832
HE LOOKS JUST LIKE YOU, ROVER.

10:58.962 --> 10:59.920
-HE'S A GOOD LOOKING KID.

11:00.050 --> 11:01.008
[LAUGHS]

11:01.138 --> 11:03.140
-WHY DO YOU CALL HIM ROVER?

11:03.271 --> 11:04.228
-WHY DO I CALL HIM ROVER?

11:04.359 --> 11:06.187
WELL, WHEN HE WAS A KID,

11:06.317 --> 11:07.536
HE USED TO TAG ALONG WITH THE
BIG KIDS, LIKE A LITTLE PUPPY.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.538
-YEAH, IT WOULD DRIVE YOU NUTS.

11:09.669 --> 11:11.714
-WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:11.845 --> 11:14.456
-WHAT? YOU EXPECT ME TO WAIT
IN THAT VAN ALL DAY, OR WHAT?

11:14.586 --> 11:16.458
-I WANTED IT TO BE A SURPRISE.

11:16.980 --> 11:21.463
HOBIE, THAT'S YOUR COUSIN KYLE.

11:21.593 --> 11:23.030
-PLEASED TO MEET YOU, MAN.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.467
-HE'S MY SON. [CHUCKLES]

11:26.686 --> 11:27.469
-HEY!

11:27.599 --> 11:28.949
[LAUGHS]

11:29.079 --> 11:29.906
-HEY.

11:32.256 --> 11:33.518
[LAUGHS]

11:39.916 --> 11:41.744
-HOW COME YOU NEVER
TOLD ME ABOUT HIM?

11:42.527 --> 11:46.488
-[SIGHS] I SUPPOSE BECAUSE
HIS MOTHER NEVER SAID ANYTHING.

11:48.185 --> 11:50.361
REMEMBER I WAS LIVIN' UP
IN BIG SUR IN THAT COMMUNE?

11:52.320 --> 11:53.756
AND, WELL, THERE WAS
THIS LADY UP THERE.

11:54.496 --> 11:57.542
FELECIA. GOD, SHE WAS BEAUTIFUL.

11:58.239 --> 11:59.370
SHE LOOKED LIKE JULIE CHRISTIE.

12:01.111 --> 12:03.418
ANYWAY, WE DUG EACH
OTHER AND, YOU KNOW ME.

12:03.548 --> 12:06.682
I'M NOT ONE FOR STAYING
IN A PLACE TOO LONG,

12:07.335 --> 12:08.162
ESPECIALLY FOR A CHICK.

12:11.165 --> 12:13.471
SHE NEVER SAID ANYTHING ABOUT
BEING PREGNANT BEFORE I SPLIT,

12:13.602 --> 12:15.430
AND I NEVER HEARD
FROM HER AGAIN.

12:18.650 --> 12:20.000
-HOW'D YOU FIND OUT ABOUT HIM?

12:21.044 --> 12:22.567
-SHE DIED THREE MONTHS AGO.

12:22.698 --> 12:24.656
THEY TRACKED ME DOWN AT
BELL'S BEACH IN AUSTRALIA.

12:26.180 --> 12:30.184
SO I CAME BACK, PICKED
HIM UP. HE'S MINE.

12:32.490 --> 12:36.712
-UH, NO OFFENSE OR
ANYTHING, BUT UH, YOU SURE?

12:37.365 --> 12:38.105
-THAT HE'S MY SON?

12:38.235 --> 12:39.236
-YEAH.

12:40.107 --> 12:41.238
-YOU GOTTA SEE HIM SURF.

12:41.369 --> 12:43.327
[CHUCKLES]

12:43.458 --> 12:47.244
-UNREAL. UNREAL!

12:47.375 --> 12:51.596
THE BUZZ MAN IS A POPPA. HAH!

12:55.035 --> 12:56.036
HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT THAT?

12:56.166 --> 12:58.690
I MEAN, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

13:02.303 --> 13:03.304
-BEATS THE HELL OUTTA ME.

13:03.434 --> 13:04.740
-NO, I'M SERIOUS.

13:05.785 --> 13:07.264
-I KNOW YOU'RE SERIOUS.

13:07.395 --> 13:08.700
YOU'RE ALWAYS SERIOUS.
YOU WERE BORN SERIOUS.

13:10.790 --> 13:12.313
I'M THE ONLY SCREW-UP
IN THIS FAMILY.

13:15.098 --> 13:15.969
HEY, LOOK, MITCH.

13:17.448 --> 13:19.015
I DIDN'T COME TO TALK
ABOUT MY PROBLEMS.

13:19.146 --> 13:22.192
I CAME TO SEE MY
BRO, GET SOME WAVES.

13:23.803 --> 13:26.196
LET THESE TWO KIDS GET
TO KNOW ONE ANOTHER.

13:27.981 --> 13:30.505
-OH. HEY, I'M GONNA
POP A CHILL. WANT ONE?

13:31.332 --> 13:32.159
-WHAT'S A CHILL?

13:32.768 --> 13:35.031
-A BEER. HOW OLD
ARE YOU, ANYWAY?

13:35.162 --> 13:37.251
-TEN AND A HALF, ALMOST ELEVEN.

13:37.381 --> 13:38.556
[BEER TOP FIZZES]

13:38.687 --> 13:41.037
