28:38.804 --> 28:39.935
-WHAT ARTICLE?

28:43.112 --> 28:45.985
-YOU ARE NOT THE PUBLISHER
OF MY NEWSPAPER. I AM.

28:46.115 --> 28:47.987
-KAY, YOU SAID YOU WERE
GOING TO RUN THE STORY.

28:48.117 --> 28:49.118
WHAT HAPPENED?

28:49.249 --> 28:50.554
-I MADE AN EDITORIAL DECISION.

28:50.685 --> 28:52.165
-WELL, IF YOU DON'T MIND,

28:52.295 --> 28:53.644
I'D LIKE TO KNOW WHAT
PROMPTED THE DECISION.

28:53.775 --> 28:55.777
OR IS THE UPCOMING
VENICE PLEASURE FAIR

28:55.908 --> 28:57.648
YOUR IDEA OF
HARD-HITTING JOURNALISM?

28:57.779 --> 29:01.609
-OKAY. I WAS PAID A VISIT BY
THE ATTORNEY FOR THE OWNERS.

29:02.262 --> 29:03.872
-SO WHAT? WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

29:04.917 --> 29:06.570
-HE HAPPENS TO BE MY FATHER.

29:07.833 --> 29:09.095
-YOUR FATHER?
-KAY: MHMM.

29:10.400 --> 29:12.054
-ELLIS MORGAN IS YOUR FATHER?

29:12.185 --> 29:14.448
-YEAH. HE SAID HE SPOKE
TO YOU ON THE PHONE.

29:14.578 --> 29:16.145
-YEAH. HE DID, A
COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO,

29:16.276 --> 29:17.668
AND HE WASN'T VERY HELPFUL.

29:17.799 --> 29:19.192
-THIS IS THE FIRST
TIME IN MY ENTIRE LIFE

29:19.322 --> 29:20.889
THAT HE'S EVER ASKED
ME FOR A FAVOR.

29:21.977 --> 29:23.196
-IT'S NOT ABOUT FAVORS.

29:23.805 --> 29:24.980
YOU SAW WHAT HAPPENED
TO THAT SURFER, KAY.

29:25.111 --> 29:26.721
IT'S ABOUT SAVING LIVES.

29:26.852 --> 29:28.941
-I KNOW WHAT IT'S ABOUT,
MITCH, AS DOES MY FATHER.

29:29.071 --> 29:30.551
HE'S JUST TRYING TO
REACH A SETTLEMENT

29:30.681 --> 29:32.205
THAT ALL THE PARTIES
CAN AGREE TO,

29:32.335 --> 29:33.641
AND HE THOUGHT IF
I RAN THE STORY

29:33.772 --> 29:36.035
IT MIGHT JEOPARDIZE
THE NEGOTIATION.

29:36.165 --> 29:38.298
-I DON'T BUY ANY OF IT. YOUR
DAD'S JUST ANOTHER ATTORNEY.

29:38.428 --> 29:39.429
IT'S A STALL TACTIC.

29:41.605 --> 29:43.477
-STAY AWAY FROM THE PIER.

29:48.047 --> 29:51.137
ANYONE SURFING IN THIS AREA
WILL BE SUBJECT TO ARREST.

29:52.181 --> 29:54.183
THE PIER HAS BEEN CONDEMNED.

29:57.665 --> 30:01.147
TAKE YOUR BOARDS AND LEAVE
THE AREA IMMEDIATELY.

30:03.453 --> 30:07.414
DO NOT ATTEMPT TO SURF THESE
WAVES OR YOU WILL BE ARRESTED.

30:07.544 --> 30:09.068
-SEE, I TOLD YA.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

30:09.198 --> 30:12.419
-WAIT A MINUTE. I
WANT TO CHECK THIS OUT.

30:12.549 --> 30:14.813
-THE PIER HAS BEEN CONDEMNED.

30:16.858 --> 30:20.470
ANYONE SURFING IN THIS
AREA WILL BE ARRESTED.

30:21.645 --> 30:22.821
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

30:26.085 --> 30:27.913
-HEY, HOBE.
SOMEONE'S AT THE DOOR!

30:36.138 --> 30:37.574
-HEY, EDDIE.
-EDDIE: HEY, HOBE.

30:39.098 --> 30:40.186
CAN I COME IN?

30:40.316 --> 30:41.013
-YEAH, SURE.
-EDDIE: GREAT.

30:41.883 --> 30:42.928
IS YOUR DAD AROUND?

30:43.450 --> 30:45.017
-UH, NO, BUT HE SHOULD
BE HERE PRETTY SOON.

30:46.540 --> 30:47.541
-KYLE, HOW'S IT GOING?

30:49.282 --> 30:51.762
[SIGHS] HEY, YOU KNOW, I MISSED
YOU AT JUNIOR GUARDS TODAY.

30:52.676 --> 30:55.027
-OH, YEAH, SORRY ABOUT
THAT. I SHOULD'VE CALLED.

30:55.679 --> 30:57.072
-YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW,

30:57.203 --> 30:58.813
I WAS JUST WORRIED
ABOUT YA, THAT'S ALL.

30:58.944 --> 30:59.292
I JUST THOUGHT MAYBE SOMETHING
MIGHT'VE HAPPENED TO YA.

30:59.945 --> 31:01.033
-OH, NO. WE WENT SURFING.

31:01.163 --> 31:02.382
-OH, YEAH? WHERE'D YOU GO?

31:03.209 --> 31:04.993
-UH, SUNSET BEACH.

31:08.388 --> 31:10.651
-SURFING TWO PLACES AT ONE
TIME. THAT'S A GOOD TRICK.

31:13.784 --> 31:14.916
I SAW YOU AT THE PIER.

31:16.875 --> 31:17.963
-YOU WERE IN THE BOAT?

31:19.616 --> 31:21.401
-SO, WHAT? ARE YOU
GONNA TELL HIS OLD MAN?

31:21.531 --> 31:24.143
-NO. HE IS.

31:25.144 --> 31:26.145
-BUT HE'LL KILL ME.

31:27.102 --> 31:29.931
-[SIGHS] LOOK, HOBE.

31:32.020 --> 31:32.978
I KNOW YOUR DAD.

31:33.804 --> 31:35.632
I KNOW HOW HE FEELS
ABOUT YOU. HE LOVES YOU.

31:36.720 --> 31:37.765
AND HE TRUSTS YOU.

31:39.245 --> 31:40.855
AND THAT'S WHY YOU
GOTTA TELL HIM THE TRUTH

31:40.986 --> 31:42.248
BECAUSE IF YOU DON'T,
YOU'RE GONNA BLOW THAT TRUST

31:42.378 --> 31:43.510
AND THINGS WILL
NEVER BE THE SAME.

31:43.640 --> 31:44.772
[SCOFFS]

31:44.903 --> 31:45.816
SAME GOES FOR YOU.

31:46.687 --> 31:48.471
-WHAT?

31:48.602 --> 31:49.908
I'M SUPPOSE TO TRUST A GUY WHO
DOESN'T EVEN KNOW WHO I AM?

31:50.473 --> 31:51.692
OR EVEN CARE?

31:51.822 --> 31:52.693
-WHY DON'T YOU
GIVE HIM A CHANCE?

31:52.823 --> 31:54.086
IT'S A TWO-WAY STREET.

31:54.695 --> 31:56.305
WHY DON'T YOU GIVE A LITTLE
INSTEAD OF TAKING ALL THE TIME?

32:00.048 --> 32:03.051
-HI, GUYS. HEY,
EDDIE. WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

32:03.182 --> 32:05.053
-NOTHING. I JUST
STOPPED BY TO SAY HI.

32:05.575 --> 32:06.576
-STAY FOR DINNER?

32:06.707 --> 32:07.621
-YOU COOKIN'?

32:08.709 --> 32:10.058
-YEAH, I'M COOKIN'.

32:10.189 --> 32:11.799
-EH, I DON'T THINK SO,
MAN. I'LL SEE YA LATER.

32:11.930 --> 32:12.887
-WELL, THANK YOU.

32:14.106 --> 32:15.063
WHERE'S BUZZ?

32:15.194 --> 32:16.369
-PARTYING WITH SOME BABE.

32:18.588 --> 32:19.676
-WHEN'S HE COMING BACK?

32:20.547 --> 32:21.504
-DON'T ASK ME.

32:23.985 --> 32:24.855
-LATER, DAD.

32:29.991 --> 32:31.775
[FIRE CRACKLES]

32:34.300 --> 32:36.258
[PHONE RINGS]

32:50.185 --> 32:51.056
-YEAH, HELLO?

32:51.186 --> 32:52.013
-BUZZ: MITCH.

32:54.668 --> 32:56.409
-BUZZ, WHERE ARE YOU?

32:56.539 --> 32:58.106
-BUZZ: SAN CLEMENTE.
I'VE HAD A COUPLE BEERS.

32:58.237 --> 32:59.455
I DON'T THINK I
SHOULD BE ON THE ROAD.

32:59.586 --> 33:01.283
-OH, MAN. DON'T DO THIS TO ME.

33:01.414 --> 33:02.197
-BUZZ: WHAT?

33:02.328 --> 33:03.546
-YOUR DIRTY WORK.

33:04.634 --> 33:06.375
LOOK, I'VE GOT MY HANDS
FULL WITH MY OWN LIFE.

33:06.506 --> 33:08.073
KYLE'S YOUR RESPONSIBILITY.

33:08.203 --> 33:09.683
-BUZZ: I DON'T KNOW WHAT
TO DO WITH HIM, MITCH.

33:09.813 --> 33:11.250
-YOU CAN START BY GETTIN'
YOUR BUTT BACK HERE.

33:11.990 --> 33:12.991
-BUZZ: I'LL BE THERE BY NOON.

33:13.121 --> 33:14.557
CAN YOU HANDLE HIM UNTIL THEN?

33:14.688 --> 33:18.692
-[SIGHS] SURE. SURE,
I GUESS I'LL HAVE TO.

33:33.924 --> 33:35.883
[PAN SIZZLING]

33:41.845 --> 33:43.412
-MORNING, HOBE.
-HOBIE: MORNING, DAD.

33:43.543 --> 33:44.370
-HOW DO YOU WANT YOUR EGGS?

33:44.892 --> 33:46.154
-UH, SCRAMBLED, I GUESS.

33:46.285 --> 33:47.547
-GOOD. GRAB SOME
BUTTER, WOULD YA?

33:47.677 --> 33:48.591
-YEAH, SURE.

33:52.291 --> 33:54.554
-YOU NOTICE THERE'S TWO CANS
OF BEER MISSIN' FROM IN THERE?

33:54.684 --> 33:55.729
YOU KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT THAT?

33:55.859 --> 33:57.296
-NO. I SWEAR.

33:59.950 --> 34:01.648
-YOU THINK KYLE KNOWS
ANYTHING ABOUT THAT?

34:03.215 --> 34:05.347
-WELL, MAYBE. I MEAN,
I CAN'T SAY FOR SURE.

34:07.567 --> 34:08.784
-SOMETHING YOU'RE
NOT TELLIN' ME?

34:11.266 --> 34:14.443
-WELL, IT'S NOT ABOUT THE BEER.

34:16.315 --> 34:17.925
IT'S JUST THAT YESTERDAY,

34:18.056 --> 34:20.058
KYLE WANTED ME TO GO
TO THE PIER WITH HIM.

34:20.928 --> 34:23.583
SO I CUT JUNIOR LIFEGUARDS
AND I WENT WITH HIM,

34:23.713 --> 34:25.933
BUT I DIDN'T SURF
THERE OR ANYTHING.

34:26.063 --> 34:28.239
I JUST WANTED TO TRY
AND TALK HIM OUT OF IT.

34:29.980 --> 34:32.418
-THINK IT'S ABOUT TIME I
HAD A LITTLE TALK WITH KYLE.

34:32.547 --> 34:35.420
-WAIT A MINUTE, DAD. HE'S
NOT AS BAD AS YOU THINK.

34:36.465 --> 34:38.206
HE'S JUST GOT A LOT OF PROBLEMS.

34:38.728 --> 34:40.643
-I KNOW, HOBIE. I KNOW.

34:44.734 --> 34:45.605
-KYLE?

34:48.563 --> 34:49.435
COME ON, KY--

34:50.217 --> 34:52.916
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

35:00.402 --> 35:02.230
[TIRES SCREECH]

35:09.759 --> 35:12.153
[WAVES CRASHING]

35:15.025 --> 35:16.549
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

35:16.679 --> 35:18.942
[WAVES CRASHING]

35:22.337 --> 35:24.992
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

35:27.690 --> 35:30.737
[WAVES CRASHING]

35:43.010 --> 35:45.317
[DRAMATIC MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

35:52.019 --> 35:54.630
[WAVES CRASHING ON PILINGS]

36:22.397 --> 36:24.530
[WAVES CRASHING ON PILINGS]

36:26.619 --> 36:28.621
[INTENSE MUSIC]

36:42.156 --> 36:45.377
[WAVES CRASHING]

36:53.950 --> 36:57.650
[SIREN WAILING]

37:12.534 --> 37:13.666
-OKAY.

37:14.754 --> 37:16.973
YOU GOT HIM BREATHING, BUT
HE'S STILL UNCONSCIOUS.

37:17.104 --> 37:17.887
-LET'S GET HIM DOWN.

37:18.018 --> 37:19.193
OKAY, ON THREE.

37:19.324 --> 37:21.195
ONE, TWO, THREE.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.892
-OKAY, EASY.

37:24.285 --> 37:26.722
-ALL RIGHT, READY?
AND UP. LET'S GO.

37:28.333 --> 37:30.291
-LADY ON SPEAKER: DR.
KIRCHY TO EMERGENCY.

37:30.422 --> 37:32.641
DR. KIRCHY TO EMERGENCY, PLEASE.

37:36.254 --> 37:37.690
-HEY, MITCH. HOW IS HE?

37:39.648 --> 37:41.520
-HE'S IN A COMA.
IT'S TOUCH AND GO.

37:42.129 --> 37:44.218
-LADY ON SPEAKER:
MR. ROSENBERGER
TO MEDICAL RECORDS.

37:44.349 --> 37:47.526
-[SIGHS] HOW LONG WAS HE UNDER?

37:49.354 --> 37:50.877
-ABOUT TWO TO THREE MINUTES.

37:52.182 --> 37:54.707
HIS BLOOD GAS LEVEL
WENT DOWN TO 25.

37:55.534 --> 37:56.665
-THAT'S RIGHT ON THE
EDGE OF BRAIN DAMAGE.

37:56.796 --> 37:57.840
-I KNOW.

37:59.755 --> 38:01.279
WE'RE NOT GONNA KNOW ANYTHING
UNTIL HE COMES OUT OF IT.

38:01.409 --> 38:02.889
-SO WHERE'S BUZZY?

38:05.631 --> 38:07.720
-SOMEWHERE BETWEEN
HERE AND SAN CLEMENTE.

38:09.852 --> 38:10.897
-YOU MEAN, HE DOESN'T KNOW?

38:11.027 --> 38:11.898
-NO.

38:12.028 --> 38:14.422
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

38:26.478 --> 38:28.001
-ANY CHANGE IN HIS CONDITION?

38:29.002 --> 38:30.438
-NO. HEY!

38:31.004 --> 38:33.049
-HE CAME BY HEADQUARTERS. I
FILLED HIM IN ON THE WAY OVER.

38:33.180 --> 38:34.268
-GOD, ARE YOU OKAY?

38:35.138 --> 38:36.096
-I THOUGHT YOU WERE
KEEPIN' AN EYE ON HIM.

38:36.226 --> 38:37.271
WHAT WAS HE DOIN' OUT THERE?

38:37.402 --> 38:38.403
-WHAT?

38:38.533 --> 38:40.013
-WHAT WAS HE DOING OUT THERE?

38:40.143 --> 38:41.493
-OH, DON'T LAY THIS ON ME, MAN.

38:42.145 --> 38:43.669
IT'S YOUR SON WE'RE
TALKIN' ABOUT.

38:44.496 --> 38:46.454
BUZZ, I WAS THE ONE
WHO BROUGHT HIM IN.

38:47.020 --> 38:48.326
WHERE THE HELL WERE YOU?

38:48.456 --> 38:49.544
-OH, YOU'RE A REAL
HERO, HUH, MITCH?

38:49.675 --> 38:51.329
-JUST, SHUT UP, HUH.

38:52.286 --> 38:53.331
-WHAT IF HE DIES?

38:53.461 --> 38:54.680
-WHAT IF HE LIVES?

38:55.420 --> 38:57.770
CAN YOU HANDLE THAT?
CAN YOU GROW UP?

38:57.900 --> 38:59.815
[GRUNTING]

38:59.946 --> 39:00.773
-MITCH, COME ON.

39:00.903 --> 39:02.122
COME ON. MITCH.

39:04.385 --> 39:05.691
COME ON, COME ON.

39:08.520 --> 39:10.391
[HEAVY BREATHING]

39:12.350 --> 39:13.655
YOU GOTTA GET IT TOGETHER.

39:15.657 --> 39:16.702
-MISTER JIM BUCHANNON.

39:17.355 --> 39:18.704
YOUR SON'S REGAINED
CONSCIOUSNESS.

39:18.834 --> 39:20.967
ALL INDICATIONS ARE
HE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

39:23.578 --> 39:25.928
[MONITOR BEEPING]

39:38.419 --> 39:40.769
-HEY, KYLE.

39:42.467 --> 39:43.381
-HEY, BUZZ.

39:46.340 --> 39:48.255
-[SIGHS] BOY,
YOU'RE A TOUGH KID.

39:48.386 --> 39:50.300
YOU'RE PROBABLY
GONNA DRIVE ME NUTS.

39:52.564 --> 39:54.957
I JUST FIGURED YOU'RE MY KARMA
FOR WHAT I DID TO MY FOLKS.

39:56.916 --> 40:00.746
HEY, LOOK. I DON'T KNOW WHAT
KIND OF LIFE WE'RE GONNA LIVE,

40:00.876 --> 40:05.751
BUT I PROMISE YOU, FROM NOW
ON, IT'S YOU AND ME TOGETHER.

40:08.884 --> 40:10.364
-YOU KNOW, I'M THIRSTY.

40:12.801 --> 40:14.455
YOU WANNA GET A NURSE
TO GET ME A COKE?

40:17.284 --> 40:18.416
-HOW ABOUT SOME MILK, HUH?

40:24.378 --> 40:25.945
-WHATEVER YOU SAY, DAD.

40:27.903 --> 40:28.948
[CHUCKLES]

40:32.604 --> 40:33.822
[KNOCKS]

40:34.475 --> 40:35.737
-GOT A MINUTE?

40:35.868 --> 40:37.478
-YEAH. YEAH, SURE. COME ON IN.

40:38.348 --> 40:40.394
-UM, HOW'S YOUR NEPHEW?

40:41.526 --> 40:43.702
-HE'S DOIN' FINE, THANKS.

40:43.832 --> 40:45.094
-THAT'S GOOD.

40:45.660 --> 40:47.619
YOU KNOW, I FELT TERRIBLE
WHEN I HEARD WHAT HAPPENED,

40:47.749 --> 40:49.577
LIKE I WAS RESPONSIBLE.

40:50.186 --> 40:51.927
-BELIEVE ME, IT
WAS NOT YOUR FAULT.

40:52.058 --> 40:55.627
-I KNOW, I JUST, WELL, I
SHOULD'VE RUN THE STORY.

40:56.541 --> 40:59.805
-KAY, IT WAS YOUR DAD. I
MEAN, THAT'S A TOUGH CALL.

41:00.849 --> 41:02.677
-I SPOKE WITH MY
FATHER THIS MORNING

41:03.504 --> 41:05.245
AND THEY REACHED A SETTLEMENT.

41:05.767 --> 41:07.856
DEMOLITION STARTS TOMORROW.

41:07.987 --> 41:10.250
-TERRIFIC! THANK HIM FOR ME.

41:10.380 --> 41:11.643
-YEAH, I WILL.

41:12.644 --> 41:14.428
SO DOES THIS MEAN
WE'RE STILL FRIENDS?

41:16.343 --> 41:17.170
-I HOPE SO.

41:18.476 --> 41:20.260
DON'T I OWE YOU A HOT
DOG, OR SOMETHIN'?

41:21.130 --> 41:22.044
-I THINK SO.

41:22.175 --> 41:23.655
[LAUGHS]

41:26.092 --> 41:30.009
-YOU KNOW, IF IT WASN'T FOR
YOU, KYLE WOULD'VE BEEN DEAD.

41:31.489 --> 41:32.707
-SOMETIMES WE GET LUCKY.

41:33.229 --> 41:35.580
-IT WASN'T LUCK,
DAD. IT WAS YOU.

41:37.190 --> 41:38.060
-THANKS, PAL.

41:45.154 --> 41:46.286
-I LOVE YOU, DAD.

41:48.157 --> 41:51.117
AND I PROMISE THAT
EVERY TIME YOU TELL ME

41:52.510 --> 41:53.902
TO MAKE MY BED,

41:54.033 --> 41:57.210
OR DRINK MY MILK, I
WON'T EVER COMPLAIN.

42:00.474 --> 42:01.736
-HOW ABOUT DOIN' YOUR HOMEWORK?

42:01.867 --> 42:02.650
-DON'T PUSH IT.

42:02.781 --> 42:04.522
-YOU! [LAUGHS]

42:05.697 --> 42:10.136
-UH, OH. WHOA.

42:14.662 --> 42:17.056
-SO, UH, WHAT'S UP
WITH YOU AND KAY?

42:17.186 --> 42:18.448
YOU GONNA ASK HER OUT, OR WHAT?

42:19.145 --> 42:21.147
-HM. THINK I SHOULD?

42:21.277 --> 42:22.801
-WELL, SHE'S PRETTY HOT.

42:23.845 --> 42:25.760
-REALLY? MAYBE YOU
SHOULD ASK HER OUT.

42:25.891 --> 42:26.805
-MAYBE I WILL.

42:26.935 --> 42:28.197
BESIDES,

42:28.763 --> 42:30.809
SHE PROBABLY DOESN'T WANT
TO GO OUT WITH YOU, ANYWAY.

42:30.939 --> 42:32.027
-REALLY?
-REALLY.

42:32.158 --> 42:32.985
-GOODBYE.
[YELLING]

42:41.689 --> 42:43.343
[END THEME PLAYING]
